    • Method Detail

      • apply

        boolean apply(T inputParam)
        Applies this predicate to the inputParam and returns true of false.
        • The evaluation of a predicate shoud not cause any side effect.
        • The result of apply should be consistent with (do not confuse with "equal to") Object.equals: a.equals(b) implies that predicate.apply(a) == predicate.apply(b)) and vice-versa.
        Parameters:
        inputParam - The input parameter on which this predicate is applied.
        Returns:
        The boolean value to which this predicate evaluates.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if inputParam is null and this predicate does not accept a null parameter.
